TITLE: Russian missile kills 7 and injures 90 in northern Ukrainian city amid local holiday
SUMMARY: Many residents had just finished a morning of festivities and were leaving church in Chernihiv, north of Kyiv, when a Russian missile struck the city's center, heavily damaging a theater building.

TITLE: A male mosquito's hairy ears tune into mates. New research suggests we can stop that
SUMMARY: If the guy skeeters can't hear the buzz of females ... no mating, no new generations. The results of a study on mosquito hearing could lead to a different kind of population control tool.

TITLE: PHOTOS: Global heat hacks, from jazzy umbrellas in DRC to ice beans in Singapore
SUMMARY: We asked photographers around the world to make pictures of how the locals cope with this year's record heat. They created some really cool images.

TITLE: Russia and India are landing on the moon next week. Here's what you need to know
SUMMARY: India and Russia are sending landers to spots near the south pole, which has water ice that might one day be mined to make rocket fuel.

TITLE: Corporate DEI initiatives are facing cutbacks and legal attacks
SUMMARY: Corporate DEI positions soared after the murder of George Floyd in 2020. Now, due to economic pressure and political pressure from the right, they face an uncertain future.

TITLE: 3 works in translation tell tales of standing up to right wrongs
SUMMARY: Itamar Vieira Junior's Crooked Plow, Miroslav Krleža's On the Edge of Reason, and Maru Ayase's The Forest Brims Over

TITLE: These poems by Latin American women reflect a multilingual region
SUMMARY: Sandra Guzmán once heard an alarming statistic: Every 14 days, an Indigenous language dies around the world. So she created a new multilingual project centered on Latin American women.

TITLE: Pickleball, the fastest growing sport in the country, is moving indoors
SUMMARY: Pickleball is the fastest growing sport in the country. Indoor courts are popping up all over, from former warehouses, to empty stores and even shopping malls.

TITLE: Small Kansas paper raided by police has a history of hard-hitting reporting
Hurricane Hilary prompts flood watch from Mexico to north of Los Angeles
SUMMARY: Hurricane Hilary continues her march toward Baja California, and people on both sides of the U.S.-Mexico border are getting ready for projected heavy rains and flooding.

TITLE: Heat dome over Central U.S. could bring hottest temps yet to parts of the Midwest
SUMMARY: This summer has already been awfully hot in the southern Plains and the Gulf Coast. Now, a large portion of the U.S. will face a prolonged period of dangerous heat.

TITLE: After 19 years, the Tuohys say they plan to terminate Michael Oher's conservatorship
SUMMARY: Lawyers for Sean and Leigh Anne Tuohy say the couple intends to end their conservatorship for Oher, a former NFL offensive lineman and the inspiration behind the 2009 film, <em>The Blind Side.

TITLE: Another Disney princess, another online outrage. This time it's about 'Snow White'
SUMMARY: Rachel Zegler finds herself at the center of another Disney princess outrage. But the way this particular one came about demonstrates the inner workings of a fine-tuned cycle for whipping up fury.

TITLE: Chikungunya virus surges in South America. But a new discovery could help outfox it
SUMMARY: South America has seen a quarter million cases this year, as climate change is a boon for the mosquitoes that spread it. A study about how the virus infects cells could help inform future treatments.

TITLE: World chess just placed restrictions on both trans women and trans men
SUMMARY: The International Chess Federation will stop allowing transgender women to participate in women's tournaments. The group said changing genders has a "significant impact" on a player's status.
